	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Jun 2nd 4:54 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=166680><span id= >Kraixz</span></a><br><span id=notbold>12 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>You are basically right about the lore part being to prevent people from farming items and selling them off. And in the case of some items (earrings, bracelets) to keep people from wearing two of the same very powerful items. It forces people to find another place to get a different item. No drop it used for a few reasons. I don't put too much stake in the idea that it is to prevent people from losing it, or if tghat is the case it is a stupid reason. If you are on a PvP server (I am) you should have to risk any and all items you have. I think it is more to prevent people from introducing very powerful weapons into the economy, and to cut back on twinking. True there are many items that can still be used to twink, but it does prevent some very powerful items from being given to low level characters, sold, and then the money used to buy entire sets of uber gear.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
