	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=95215><span id=Scholar>Kothall</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>133 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Actually Lore was started as a user request to them.&nbsp;&nbsp;I doubt you'll find any &quot;LORE PENDING&quot; pics on this site anymore but that was when the change over was made for many items...<br><br>Back in the long ago days, farming was fierce at times for 'uber' gear.  Some folks would spend days just farming a good piece of equipment over and over so they could sell it -- green farming a lot of times...  If you think it's bad now, you should have seen it back then.  Level 30's sitting in HP farming PGT's (a royally &quot;UBER&quot; item back then) and selling them.  It was set as LORE to stop the farming that many were complaining about.<br><br>You have to realize that there was no &quot;camping&quot; enforced back then.  Who ever hit it first, it was their MOB so you'd have a lot of squabbeling between players at some spots because &quot;camps&quot; did NOT have to be honored (some GM's now WILL enforce camps -- like IG's in Everfrost) 2 groups or more could easily setup and cross pull... (thus /petition THEY STOLE OUR MOB!!!)  hehe<br><br>LORE was first.  Then came in NO DROP.  Sorry but I can't recall if NO DROP was before or after PvP servers were started -- first pass there were NO PvP servers -- just 'red' and 'blue' players.  PvP showed red text, non-PvP showed blue text for their name/titles above their heads.  This is where 'red server' vs 'blue server' talk started from -- red players and blue players on the same server...<br><br>After NO DROP came trivial code which didn't work all that well.  There were nice quests that couldn't be done when it was first introduced.  They tried to 'tweak' the code but it had a lot of problems and the zones it was built into were left pretty vacant for the most part so it's pretty much been dumped.<br><br>Then comes the level limits on proc's.  Then level limits on equipping things then level limits stat wise on equipment -- Required vs Recommended and the confusion this has generated from time to time.<br><br>All of it is just trying to balance out the game so folks can play without the overt 'uber twinking' so you end up with level 1's running around in level 65 gear that unbalances the world for everyone...<br><br>Anyhow, yeah I played before SolA zone existed...  back when you actually HAD to /petition for your last name at level 20 and before there was even the quests for warrior armor in the Karana's (crafted).  I remember a bunch of stuff from back then and the game has changed a lot since those days...  IMHO it's gotten better for the most part and, knowing the past, some quirks from all the adjusting that they've done to &quot;balance the game&quot; are rather humerous to see folks try and explain at times ;)<br><br>Kothall Landrunner<br>61st Level Druid</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
